  <bioghist id="aspace_9d0e61febc42f82c52b08a8bdbafc6d8">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Patrick Joseph Sullivan was born in New York City on March 18, 1874 to Patrick J. Sullivan and Ellen O'Brien Sullivan, both of whom had emigrated from Ireland in the mid-19th century.</p><p>By 1905, Sullivan was working for the NYC Department of Education as fuel inspector, a job he would hold for the rest of his life. On November 9, 1910, he married Mary (Mamie) Coughlin at St. Monica's Roman Catholic Church in Manhattan. The couple soon settled in Corona, Queens, where they raised 9 children: Frank, Madeleine, Honoria (Nonie), Rosemary, James, Alice, Daniel, Geraldine, and Joan.</p><p>Patrick Joseph Sullivan died suddenly on February 23, 1944. </p>  </bioghist>
